        {
          "id": "hipaa_brochure",
          "title": "What is HIPAA?",
          "type": "document",
          "x": 15,
          "y": 4,
          "fact": "HIPAA — the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 — isn't just about privacy. It has five titles, but Title II is the one that matters to you: it sets national standards for protecting patient health information (PHI). Two key rules: the Privacy Rule (who can see PHI) and the Security Rule (how to protect electronic PHI). Every person in this hospital — from the CEO to the janitor — has a role in keeping patient data safe."
        }
      ],
