          "title": "De-identification: The Safe Harbor",
          "type": "poster",
          "x": 8,
          "y": 1,
          "fact": "HIPAA allows sharing health data freely if it's properly de-identified. The Safe Harbor method requires removing all 18 identifiers. The Expert Determination method uses a statistician to certify re-identification risk is 'very small.' De-identified data isn't PHI — and isn't subject to HIPAA rules."
        }
      ],
