          "type": "poster",
          "x": 10,
          "y": 1,
          "fact": "HIPAA doesn't disappear in emergencies — but it flexes. Providers can share PHI without authorization when necessary to treat the patient, to prevent a serious threat to health or safety, or to assist in disaster relief. The key word is 'necessary.' Even in a crisis, share only what's needed for the situation at hand."
