        {
          "id": "emergency_exceptions",
          "title": "When You CAN Share PHI",
          "type": "whiteboard",
          "x": 17,
          "y": 12,
          "fact": "HIPAA isn't trying to STOP healthcare—it just wants you to be thoughtful. You can share PHI without patient authorization for: Treatment, Payment, Operations (TPO - The Holy Trinity), Required by Law (court orders, mandatory reporting), Public Health (disease outbreaks), Law Enforcement (court orders, subpoenas, for suspect identification, crime on premises, or medical emergencies—a warrant isn't always required), Deceased Persons (coroners, funeral directors), and Emergencies. The Catch: Even when permitted, still use MINIMUM NECESSARY."
