        {
          "id": "minimum_necessary_manual",
          "title": "Minimum Necessary Rule",
          "type": "poster",
          "x": 17,
          "y": 8,
          "fact": "Healthcare is gossipy, but HIPAA has opinions about your oversharing habits. The Minimum Necessary Rule: Only access, use, or disclose the LEAST amount of PHI needed to get the job done. Not the most interesting amount. Not the juiciest amount. The MINIMUM. The Test: Ask yourself 'Do I NEED this to do my actual job, or do I just WANT to know?' If it's want? Close the chart. Walk away. Get a hobby."
        },
        {
          "id": "hipaa_penalties",
          "title": "HIPAA Enforcement & Penalties",
          "type": "poster",
          "x": 10,
          "y": 4,
          "fact": "Think HIPAA violations are just a slap on the wrist? Think again. Civil Penalties (per violation): Tier 1 'Didn't Know' — $100-$50K. Tier 2 'Reasonable Cause' — $1K-$50K. Tier 3 'Willful Neglect, Corrected' — $10K-$50K. Tier 4 'Willful Neglect, Not Corrected' — $50K+, up to $2.13M per year per violation category. Criminal Penalties: Up to $50K and 1 year for knowing violations. Up to $100K and 5 years for violations under false pretenses. Up to $250K and 10 years for violations with intent to sell or use PHI. And yes, individuals can be personally prosecuted — your employer's insurance won't save you."
        }
      ],
